Detailed Description

This is the root of the Abstract Syntax Tree class hierarchy.

An AstNode object represents an Abstract Syntax Tree (AST) Node. The AstNode class hierarchy is subdivided into:

  • declarations (subclasses of Declaration),
  • expressions (subclasses of Expression), and
  • statements (subclasses of Statement).

There are several types (kinds) of concrete AST nodes. More specifically, a node can be:

  • a declaration node (a subclass of Declaration) of type: DCLASS, DMETHOD, DFIELD, DPARAMETER, DVARIABLE
  • an expression node (a subclass of Expression) of type: ELITERAL, ENAME, EUNARY, EBINARY, ECAST, EMCALL,
  • a statement node (a subclass of Statement) of type: SASSIGN, SWHILE, SIF, SRETURN, SBLOCK, SMCALL, SEMPTY
